 On Friday morning the new look of Lowvelder was revealed to the public at the Mpumalanga Show. The newspaper did not just have fresh news but also sported a brand-new look. Copies of Lowvelder were handed out for free at the show and contained a seed which readers could plant. During the show, they also had the chance to enter the lucky draw to win a new Polo Vivo from Lowvelder. Ilse Grobbelaar was the lucky winner. Also read: Jimmy Stonehouse maak sy hart oop oor ISG Grobbelaar said she only entered the competition a few hours before the winner was announced. “I told my husband that we have to go to the show, because I have to enter the competition. The competition was one of the main reasons I attended,” she said.
She added that it was the first time she had won something.